---
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Blog from '../../../../layouts/blog.astro';
import '../../../../assets/files/journal.css';

export const frontmatter = {
  title: "Dead pixels",
  date: "260604",
};
---

<Layout title={frontmatter.date + " " + frontmatter.title} url="https://Loveisdancing.com/files/documents/blog/260604">

    <Blog
    
    date={frontmatter.date}
    title={frontmatter.title}
    caption="Photos by Ben Burton."
    backgroundColor="black"
    textColor="white"
    invertLogo={true}

    >
    
<!--     <div slot="image" class="blogimg"></div> -->
<!--     <img src="/content/images/dead-pixels/snarl.jpg" slot="image" class="blogimg"> -->

    <div slot="image" class="carousel">
        <div class="track">
            <div class="group">
                <div class="card"><img src="/content/images/blog/260604/max1_edit.jpg"></div>
                <div class="card"><img src="/content/images/blog/260604/max2_edit.jpg"></div>
                <div class="card"><img src="/content/images/blog/260604/max1_edit.jpg"></div>
                <div class="card"><img src="/content/images/blog/260604/max2_edit.jpg"></div>
                <div class="card"><img src="/content/images/blog/260604/max1_edit.jpg"></div>
                <div class="card"><img src="/content/images/blog/260604/max2_edit.jpg"></div>
            </div>
            <div aria-hidden class="group">
                <div class="card"><img src="/content/images/blog/260604/max1_edit.jpg"></div>
                <div class="card"><img src="/content/images/blog/260604/max2_edit.jpg"></div>
                <div class="card"><img src="/content/images/blog/260604/max1_edit.jpg"></div>
                <div class="card"><img src="/content/images/blog/260604/max2_edit.jpg"></div>
                <div class="card"><img src="/content/images/blog/260604/max1_edit.jpg"></div>
                <div class="card"><img src="/content/images/blog/260604/max2_edit.jpg"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <p slot="journal">
        I want to write. 
    </p>
        
    <p slot="journal">
        Last night I took photos with Ben Burton and it was so fun. Halfway through I started coughing like crazy and that definitely brought down my focus, but we made it! I'm so grateful to have the opportunity to work with cool people like Ben. He said something that I think will stick with me for a long time, that kind of reassured me about taking the leap to reach out which is something I haven't done much of. To not put words in his mouth, I'll just say how I kinda took it, but he said something along the lines of "I like to work with musicians because they have such big ideas." At that moment I was like "He gets it." I think not having a super clear direction for the photos worked out in our favor because we spent time experimenting. Which I love to do.
    </p>

    <p slot="journal">
        We spent a lot of time in my aunt's basement gym. The walls were covered in mirrors and I liked the gym equipment because it fits with the throughline of the HeartBeat EP which I think is "What sound does your HeartBeat?" We also made a quick stop at Alum Creek and then (and pretend you didn't read this) took some pictures in a house that was still being built in a rich neighborhood near me. We also ended it at a baseball field and I had a prosthetic that I was gonna try to wear but tbh I made it like shit and I don't think it would've been worth the time.
    </p>

    <p slot="journal">
        I started adding dead pixels to images on this site through a custom TouchDesigner patch because I thought it would look cool. Once I started adding colors (mainly the cyan) I really started diving into what HeartBeat would look like and building out the world that I see it existing in. It wasn't until writing this that I started connecting the dots and turning it into something more meaningful. 
    </p>

    <p slot="journal">
        During the shoot, I was trying my hardest not to be self-conscious. I just remind myself that everything is curated and everyone only posts things that they think they look good in. But relating this back to dead pixels... I think I found more enjoyment in the digicam and iPod Touch pics because the lower quality is a mask (me saying this as I only have the limited number of iPod Touch pics to judge the shoot off of rn). It's cynical, but I have a feeling that I won't like a majority of the high quality photos because they will be <em>too</em> me. And I can make up the excuse that I like the lower quality ones more because they showcase the world I see HeartBeat existin in, but really it's because I struggle with self-respect.
    </p>

    <p slot="journal">
        All this to say that I think the dead pixels are just another mask. They enhance the digital narrative of HeartBeat, which only exists because I'm too scared to show myself in high-res. The mistakes are too apparent.
    </p>

    <p slot="journal">
        Anyways yeah I'm being dramatic as hell because I haven't even seen a lot of the photos yet but regardless of how I feel about them, I'm glad to have worked with someone whose work I adore and I finally feel like I can do music.
    </p>

    <p slot="journal">
        #peace
    </p>

    <audio slot="audio" autoplay loop id="bgaudio">
    <source src="/content/audio/fx/dance_chords.ogg" type="audio/mpeg">
    </audio>

    </Blog>

    <script>
    var audio = document.getElementById("bgaudio") as HTMLAudioElement;
    audio.volume = 0.2;
    </script>

</Layout>